# Playwright Framework Rules

## Project structure
All paths are relative to the project root.

- `src/pages/` — page object classes (`BasePage.ts`, LoginPage.ts, RegisterPage.ts, …)
- `src/pages/index.ts` — barrel export for all page objects
- `src/page-objects/PageObjectManager.ts` — facade with lazy getters for each page
- `src/fixtures/index.ts` — extended test with pom, authenticatedPom, testUser
- `src/config/env.ts` — environment variables with Zod validation
- `src/constants/routes.ts` — all page URL paths
- `src/helpers/test-step.ts` — @TestStep decorator for HTML report steps
- `src/utils/helpers.ts` — uniqueId(), retry(), waitForRequest(), waitForResponse()
- `tests/e2e/` — spec files (*.spec.ts)
- `web/` — PawShop website HTML source files

## TypeScript path aliases
Only one alias is defined — `@/*` maps to `src/*`.

- Always use `@/` prefix for all internal imports
- Never use bare aliases without slash — `@pages/` or `@fixtures/` are invalid
- Never import `test` or `expect` from `@playwright/test` in spec files
- Check `tsconfig.json` paths section for all available aliases

## Imports

### Spec files (tests/e2e/*.spec.ts)
- Always import `test` and `expect` from `@/fixtures/index`
- Never import `test` or `expect` from `@playwright/test` in spec files
- Access all page objects via `pom` fixture — never instantiate pages directly in specs

### Page object classes (src/pages/*.ts)
- Import `Page` and `Locator` from `@playwright/test`
- Import `TestStep` from `@/helpers/test-step`
- Import `ROUTES` from `@/constants/routes`
- Never import from `@/fixtures` in page objects — causes circular imports

## Page objects
- All page objects extend `BasePage` from `@/pages/BasePage`
- If you declare a constructor, call `super(page)`; otherwise TypeScript forwards `new MyPage(page)` to `BasePage`
- One class per page — LoginPage, RegisterPage, HomePage etc.
- All locators defined as `get` properties returning `Locator`
- All public action methods decorated with `@TestStep`
- Export all pages from `src/pages/index.ts`
- Register every page in `PageObjectManager` with lazy getter

## BasePage available methods
- `navigate(path: string)` — navigate to path using baseURL
- `waitForPageLoad()` — wait for domcontentloaded and networkidle
- `fillField(locator: Locator, value: string)` — clear and fill input
- `assertVisible(locator: Locator)` — assert element is visible
- `assertText(locator: Locator, text: string)` — assert element text
- `assertURL(urlPattern: string | RegExp)` — assert current URL
- `clickAndWait(locator: Locator)` — click and wait for page load
- `waitForElement(locator: Locator, timeout?: number)` — wait for element
- `takeScreenshot(name: string)` — save screenshot

## Naming conventions
- Page object files: `LoginPage.ts`, `RegisterPage.ts`
- Spec files: `login.spec.ts`, `register.spec.ts` — one file per feature
- Locator getters: `get emailInput()`, `get submitButton()`
- Action methods: `login()`, `submitRegistration()`, `goto()`

## Locators
- Always prefer `page.getByTestId()` for all locators
- If element has no data-testid use `getByRole()`, `getByLabel()` or `getByText()`
- Use CSS selectors or XPath only as last resort
- Never hardcode selectors that could break with UI changes
- Always verify data-testid values against actual HTML in `web/` folder
- Never assume or guess data-testid values

## Fixtures
- `pom` — PageObjectManager for unauthenticated tests
- `authenticatedPom` — PageObjectManager with already logged in user
- `authenticatedPage` — raw Page with already logged in user
- `testUser` — `{ email, password }` from env variables

## Tests
- All specs go in `tests/e2e/`
- One spec file per feature area
- Always use `test.describe()` with `@regression` tag
- Each test must be fully independent — no shared state between tests
- Use `test.beforeEach()` for repeated navigation or setup
- Use `uniqueId()` from `@/utils/helpers` for unique emails and test data
- Use `testUser` fixture for passwords — never hardcode credentials
- Use `authenticatedPom` for tests that require logged in user
- Never build test data in spec file — handle in page object methods

## Routes
- Never hardcode URLs in spec files
- All page objects navigate using `ROUTES` from `@/constants/routes`
- `ROUTES` values are relative paths — Playwright uses `baseURL` from config

## Step methods (@TestStep)
- Import `TestStep` from `@/helpers/test-step`
- Decorate all public page object methods with `@TestStep`
- Simple locator getters do not need `@TestStep`
- Goal — every user action visible in HTML report and traces

## Assertions
- In spec files always use `expect` from `@/fixtures/index`
- In page objects use `expect` from `@playwright/test`
- Add short message as second argument on important assertions
- Always cover both positive and negative cases

## TypeScript
- Always use `async/await` — never `.then()` chains
- Never use `any` type
- Let TypeScript infer return types — avoid redundant `: Promise<void>`
- Type variables only when inference is unclear

## PawShop source code
- PawShop HTML files are in `web/` folder
- Always read actual HTML to find correct data-testid values
- Never assume data-testid values — always verify in HTML source
- JavaScript in HTML may add data-testid attributes dynamically
- Never modify any files in `web/` folder

## Anti-patterns — never do these
- `page.waitForTimeout()` — use locator waits or expect instead
- `page.pause()` in committed code
- Hardcoded URLs in spec files — use ROUTES
- Hardcoded credentials — use testUser fixture
- Shared state between tests
- Instantiating page objects directly in spec files
- Importing from `@playwright/test` in spec files
- Using bare aliases without `@/` prefix
- Assuming data-testid values without checking HTML source
- Modifying files in `web/` folder

## ESLint
- ESLint auto-fixes on save via `.vscode/settings.json`
- Run `npm run lint` before committing
- Never use `// eslint-disable` unless absolutely necessary
- Never use `any` type — ESLint will catch this